'''''Changing of the Gods: Feminism and the End of Traditional Religions''''' is a non-fiction book written by [[Naomi Goldenberg]].<ref name=NYT>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|title=The Uses Of Gender|author=Dinnerstein, Dorothy|date=July 29, 1979|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1979/07/29/archives/the-uses-of-gender-women.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1982/04/11/books/is-god-a-feminist.html|date=1982|author=Silk, Mark|title=Is God A Feminist?|work=The New York Times}}</ref>
==Overview== A feminist take on traditional [[androcentrism|male dominated]] [[religion]]s.
