{{Infobox book | name = Einstein's Cosmos | image = Einstein's Cosmos.jpg| caption = | author = [[Michio Kaku]] | country = [[United States]] | language = [[English language|English]] | subject = [[Physics]] | genre = [[Popular science]] | publisher = | pub_date = 2004 | media_type = | pages = | isbn = 978-0393327007 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = [[Visions (book)]] | followed_by = [[Parallel Worlds (book)]] }} '''''Einstein's Cosmos: How Albert Einstein's Vision Transformed Our Understanding of Space and Time''''' is a [[popular science]] [[book]] by [[Michio Kaku]] first published in 2004.<ref>[http://cocatalog.loc.gov/cgi-bin/Pwebrecon.cgi?Search_Arg=Einstein%27s+Cosmos&Search_Code=TALL&PID=bjGN3qEAYo2Tv0mx86RC64eU_wlrG&SEQ=20170907101907&CNT=25&HIST=1 Registration Number TX0005998658]</ref> In the book Kaku discusses [[Albert Einstein]]'s work, life and concepts such as [[Mass–energy equivalence|E=mc²]] as well as [[special relativity]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Nonfiction Book Review: EINSTEIN'S COSMOS: How Albert Einstein's Vision Transformed Our Understanding of Space and Time by Michio Kaku |url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-393-05165-0 |website=PublishersWeekly.com |accessdate=2015-10-29}}</ref>
