[[Image:Gao Xing.jpg|thumb|right|125px|Gao Xing at [[No.1 Senior High School of Urumqi|Urumqi No.1 High School]], 2007]] '''Gao Xing''' ({{zh|s=高兴|p=Gāo Xìng}}; born 1974) is a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] [[Amateur astronomy|amateur astronomer]] from [[Ürümqi]], [[Xinjiang]], [[People's Republic of China|China]]. He built Xingming Observatory (星明天文台) in 2006 and discovered Comet [[C/2008 C1]] (Chen-Gao) on February 1, 2008 with Chen Tao from [[Jiangsu]] and Comet [[P/2009 L2]] (Yang-Gao) on June 15, 2009 with [[Yang Rui (astronomer)|Yang Rui]] from [[Hangzhou]], [[Zhejiang]] and Comet [[C/2015 F5]] (SWAN-Xingming) on April 4, 2015 with Guoyou Sun from [[Wenzhou]], [[Zhejiang]]. [[People's Republic of China|China]] and hence won the [[Edgar Wilson Award]] for 2008. In the night on February 26, 2009, he discovered a nova in [[Sagittarius (constellation)|Sagittarius]] in the [[Galaxy]]'s central part at night with his partner [[Sun Guoyou]] from [[Wenzhou]].<ref>[http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/cndy/2009-06/18/content_8295479.htm Teacher discovers new star with his observatory - Chinadaily.com.cn]</ref><ref>[http://www.sciencenet.cn/m/user_content.aspx?id=239029 Star seeker: Gao Xing - www.sciencenet.cn]</ref> Gao reported his new discovery to the [[International Astronomical Union]] on May 29 and acquired the identification.In the night on October 3, 2010, he discovered a new Supernova in NGC5430 at night with his partner Sun Guoyou.He also discovered several SOHO [[comet]]s and NEAT Asteroids. Currently, he is working as a [[physics]] teacher at the [[No.1 Senior High School of Urumqi|Urumqi No.1 High School]]. He also has a daughter.
