{{italic title}} {{unreferenced|date=November 2017}} '''''Genius by Stephen Hawking''''' is a television series aired on [[PBS]] hosted by [[Stephen Hawking]]. It premiered on May 18, 2016 and ended on June 1, 2016, with only one season being produced before Hawking's death in 2018.
==Premise== ''Genius by Stephen Hawking'' is a series that first aired on [[PBS]] on Wednesdays, from May 18 to June 1, 2016. Professor Stephen Hawking challenges volunteers to think like geniuses and solve some of humanity's most enduring questions. ''What, Why, Where, are We'' (as in humanity) are covered, as well as ''Are We Alone'' and ''Can We Time Travel''. Generally three volunteers with these questions are followed as they try to find the answers to their questions. The idea is to teach the volunteers and watchers how to think like a genius. All are G-rated TV hour episodes originally aired in pairs.
