'''Peter Robert Last''' is an [[Australia]]n [[ichthyologist]], curator of the Australian National Fish Collection and a senior principal research scientist at [[CSIRO Marine and Atmospheric Research]] (CMAR) in [[Hobart]], [[Tasmania]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Peter R. Last|publisher=Harvard University Press|url=http://www.hup.harvard.edu/results-list.php?author=13514|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100729114238/http://www.hup.harvard.edu/results-list.php?author=13514|archivedate=29 July 2010|deadurl=no}}</ref> He is an  [[Elasmobranchii|elasmobranch]] expert and has described many new species of shark.<ref>{{Cite journal|author1=Ward, Robert D. |author2=Holmes, Bronwyn H. |author3=White, William T. |author4=Last, Peter R.  |lastauthoramp=yes |year=2008|title=DNA barcoding Australasian chondrichthyans: results and potential uses in conservation|journal=Marine and Freshwater Research|volume=59|issue=1|pages=57&ndash;71|doi=10.1071/MF07148}}</ref>

Last is the co-author of ''Sharks and Rays of Australia''<ref>{{Cite book|author1=Last, Peter R.  |author2=Stevens, John D. |lastauthoramp=yes |year=2009|title=Sharks and Rays of Australia|location=Cambridge, Massachusetts|publisher=Harvard University Press|isbn=978-0-674-03411-2}}</ref> and co-author of ''A revision of the Australian handfishes (Lophiiformes: Brachionichthyidae), with descriptions of three new genera and nine new species''.<ref>{{Cite book|author1=Last, Peter R.  |author2=Gledhill, Daniel C. |lastauthoramp=yes |year=2009|title=A revision of the Australian handfishes (Lophiiformes: Brachionichthyidae), with descriptions of three new genera and nine new species|series=(Zootaxa 2252)|location=Auckland, New Zealand|publisher=Magnolia Press|isbn=978-1-86977-425-7|url=http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/2009/f/zt02252p077.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101204141143/http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/2009/f/zt02252p077.pdf|archivedate=4 December 2010|deadurl=no}}</ref>

