'''Rudolph E. Schild''' (born January 10, 1940) is an [[astrophysicist]] at the [[Harvard-Smithsonian Center for Astrophysics]], who has been active since the mid-1960s.<ref name=CFA-rps>http://cfa-www.harvard.edu/~rschild/rps.html</ref> He has authored or contributed to over 250 papers, of which 150 are in refereed journals.<ref name=pub>http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-abs_connect?author=schild,r&nr_to_return=all</ref> He is married to mezzo-soprano [[Jane Struss]], who teaches voice at [[Longy School of Music]].<ref name=CFA-rps/>
Schild is a proponent of "[[magnetospheric eternally collapsing object]]s" (MECOs),<ref> {{cite journal |author1=R.E. Schild |author2=D.J. Leiter |author3=S.L. Robertson |year=2006 |title=Observations Supporting the Existence of an Intrinsic Magnetic Moment inside the Central Compact Object within the Quasar Q0957+56 |journal=[[The Astronomical Journal]] |volume=132 |pages=420–432 |arxiv=astro-ph/0505518 |bibcode=2006AJ....132..420S |doi=10.1086/504898 }}</ref><ref name=SchildMeco>{{cite journal |author=R.E. Schild |author2=D.J. Leiter |date=2010 |title=Black Hole or MECO? Decided By a Thin Luminous Ring Structure Deep Within Quasar Q0957+561 |url=http://journalofcosmology.com/SchildLeiter1.pdf |journal=[[Journal of Cosmology]] |volume=6 |issue= |pages=1400 |arxiv=0806.1748 |bibcode=2010JCos....6.1400S }}</ref> an alternative to [[black hole]]s.<ref name=theage> {{cite web |author=I. Sample |date=30 July 2006 |url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/world/us-teams-quasar-probe-sinks-black-hole-theory/2006/07/29/1153816426971.html |title=US team's quasar probe sinks black hole theory |work=The Age.com }}</ref> These results are most often published in the fringe ''[[Journal of Cosmology]]'', an astronomy journal edited by Schild himself,<ref>http://journalofcosmology.com/About.html</ref> while his other research is published in mainstream astronomy journals such as ''[[MNRAS]]'' and the ''[[Astronomical Journal]]''.<ref name=pub/>
